fields.Title: WHIRLING F3 ORB / pinball workshop
fields.Condition: Variable["auto.in_whirling_walls"] == true  and  Variable["whirling.workshop_tools"] == true  and  Variable["whirling.workshop_machine"] == true  and  Variable["whirling.workshop_boxes"] == true  and  Variable["whirling.orb_pinball_mystery_done"] == false
fields.Description:
1. This was a pinball workshop.
2. Was the Whirling-in-Rags part of the doomed commercial area task gained.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It's not a ghost story. It's a curs..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not a ghost story. It's a curse -- and Garte ought be made knowledgeable so he can perform counter-spells.

fields.Title: Logic: "This seems to be some kind of works..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This seems to be some kind of workshop. For fixing up pinball machines -- a long time ago. Everything is covered with dust now...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like it. I'm guessing Martin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like it. I'm guessing Martinaise North 22 used to be a pinball arcade before it became a hostel. There are machines left over..." He taps his foot.

fields.Title: You: ""Could this mean the Whirling-in-Ra..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could this mean the Whirling-in-Rags really *is* part of the Doomed Commercial Area?"
fields.Alternate1: "Could this mean the Whirling-in-Rags really *is* part of the Doomed Commercial Area?"

fields.Title: Logic: "As the Dicemaker said, yes; it all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As the Dicemaker said, yes; it all fits. Not that it has anything to do with the case, but it is a nice connection!

fields.Title: You: ""Doesn't look like that pinball mac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't look like that pinball machine will ever get fixed."
fields.Alternate1: Doesn't look like that pinball machine will ever get fixed.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ah, yes -- as the novelty dicemake..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, yes -- as the novelty dicemaker said." He makes a note in his notebook. "This has absolutely nothing to do with the case, I'm sure. But I do like a nice little *connection*."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Remember the *Dicemaker*?! Then tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Remember the *Dicemaker*?! Then that means...

fields.Title: You: ""Whirling-in-Rags was once the East..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whirling-in-Rags was once the East Delta Pinball arcade. This is all left over from that."

fields.Title: Logic: "So this is where they brought fault..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So this is where they brought faulty pinball machines to fix them up -- a long time ago. Everything is covered with dust now...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks around the dus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks around the dusty, crowded room, inspecting the tools on the shelf.

fields.Title: Logic: "Yes. Pinball hasn't enjoyed a heyda..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. Pinball hasn't enjoyed a heyday for fifteen or twenty years.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If that's true then our *cafeteria..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If that's true then our *cafeteria manager* is not going to like it." He looks around. "We should tell him what we found up here -- *omitting* that suspicion."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He does not appear to be the kind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He does not appear to be the kind of man who likes his establishment to be part of a neighbourhood ghost story. About *bankruptcy*."

fields.Title: Logic: "And Garte would not like that. He s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And Garte would not like that. He should probably be made aware that his establishment is part of the neighbourhood ghost story.

fields.Title: Logic: "Stupid superstition. But still -- i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stupid superstition. But still -- it would be *interesting* to see what the cafeteria manager thinks of this...

fields.Title: You: "Not interested. [Discard thought.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Not interested. [Discard thought.]

fields.Title: You: ""This used to be a... pinball works..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This used to be a... pinball workshop."
fields.Alternate1: This used to be a... pinball workshop.

fields.Title: Logic: "Yes. It would mean that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. It would mean that.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "A creak, some dust falls off a shel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A creak, some dust falls off a shelf.

fields.Title: You: ""Looks like they gave up on fixing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like they gave up on fixing the pinball machines at some point."
fields.Alternate1: Looks like they gave up on fixing the pinball machines at some point.

fields.Title: Logic: "And it has been forgotten. Now, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And it has been forgotten. Now, there is only one working machine in the main hall -- the rest is lost to dust.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "But then it went bankrupt... your s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But then it went bankrupt... your skin crawls from making the connection!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""At some point -- twenty years ago?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "At some point -- twenty years ago? Fifteen maybe. Before pinball went out of vogue."

fields.Title: Logic: "Yes. Martinaise North 22 used to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. Martinaise North 22 used to be a pinball arcade.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Downstairs in the hall -- next to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Downstairs in the hall -- next to the main door. One of them even works. I've seen one of the Hardies bang away at it."
